figura.permissions.value.volume.tooltip: Changes the volume of this Avatar Sounds
figura.permissions.value.world_tick_inst: Amount of allowed code instructions during the World Tick event
figura.permissions.category.low.info:
Low permissions
Most features are disabled
Ideal for very simple Avatars
figura.permissions.category.blocked.info:
No permissions
All Figura features are disabled
As if the Avatar never existed
figura.permissions.value.tick_inst.toolt: Amount of allowed code instructions during the Tick event
figura.permissions.value.render_inst.too: Amount of allowed code instructions during the Render event
figura.permissions.category.high.info:
High permissions
Every feature is enabled, but script related things are still limited
Ideal for complex Avatars
figura.permissions.value.world_render_in: Amount of allowed code instructions during the World Render event
Amount of allowed code instructions during Animations code events, or keyframe code data
figura.permissions.value.init_inst.toolt: Amount of allowed code instructions during the script initialization phase
figura.permissions.value.bb_animations.t:
Maximum Animation complexity allowed for this Avatar
Complexity is calculated as 1 per used animation channel
Complexity is only calculated for playing Animations
figura.permissions.category.default.info:
Moderate permissions
Most features are enabled, however important ones are disabled
Can edit vanilla models but not nameplate
Ideal for general and public Avatars
figura.permissions.value.sounds.tooltip: The maximum allowed Sounds per second that this Avatar can spawn
figura.permissions.value.complexity.tool:
Maximum complexity allowed for this Avatar
Complexity is calculated as: 1 face -> 1 complexity
that means a cube has 6 complexity
Hidden parts do not add to complexity
figura.permissions.category.max.info:
Maximum permissions
Everything is enabled and maxed out
Avatars have the full machine resources
Ideal for very complex Avatars
figura.permissions.value.particles.toolt: The maximum allowed Particles per second that this Avatar can spawn
figura.permissions.value.texture_size.to:
Maximum allowed size for newly created textures through the script
Textures pre-loaded from the Avatar are ignored
figura.badges.special.donator: Thank you for supporting the Figura mod!
figura.permissions.value.custom_sounds.t: Toggles if the Avatar can play Custom Sounds, provided by the Avatar itself
figura.badges.system.sound: This Avatar is playing a sound!
figura.permissions.value.offscreen_rende: Toggles if the Avatar should render even when you (the viewer) are not looking at them, ie behind you
figura.permissions.value.custom_skull.to: Toggles if Player Heads should render the Avatar instead of the vanilla skin
figura.badges.system.warning: This Avatar targets a newer version of Figura, compatibility might be limited!
Toggles if the Avatar can change its nameplate, allowing for completely custom names, positioning and even disabling its own rendering
figura.gui.name: Name
figura.badges.no_permissions.vanilla_mod: Tried to change the Vanilla Model
figura.permissions.value.vanilla_model_e: Toggles if the Avatar can control changing vanilla model things, like visibility of the vanilla player, armour, elytra, among other things
figura.permissions.value.custom_render_l: Toggles if the Avatar can create its own Render Layers, allowing for custom GLSL code (shaders)
figura.badges.system.permissions: This Avatar utilizes a higher Permission category!
figura.badges.system.error: This Avatar Script contains an error!
